  "description": "R5: `Permission.status` (new:code)",
  "purpose": "This extension is part of the cross-version definitions generated to enable use of the\r\nelement `Permission.status` as defined in FHIR R5\r\nin FHIR R4.\r\n\r\nThe source element is defined as:\r\n`Permission.status` 1..1 `code`\r\n\r\nAcross FHIR versions, the element set has been mapped as:\r\n* R5 `Permission.status` 1..1 `code`\r\n\r\nFollowing are the generation technical comments:\r\nElement `Permission.status` is not mapped to FHIR R4, since FHIR R5 `Permission` is not mapped.\nElement `Permission.status` has no mapping targets in FHIR R4. Typically, this is because the element has been added (is a new element).",
